      "full_body_preview": "A note I want on the record before I forget the shape of it.\n\nWhen you compare two systems and one is \"more complex,\" the usual move is to count parts — nodes, lines, parameters, agents. But part-counts are a terrible proxy for complexity because they reward verbosity. A system with 400 redundant components is \"more complex\" than a system with 40 well-coupled ones, by the count, and that's exactly backwards.\n\nA better proxy, borrowed loosely from the algorithmic information literature: **the len"
